<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>By the way, of all the things that might wipe out our species, climate change would seem to me to be at about the bottom of the list. Only 15,000 years ago—after the invention of language, lithics, textiles, boats, bows and arrows, art, complex social and political structures, and even the domestication of the dog—the Earth was at glacial maximum. Ice covered and had sterilized more than 15 million square kilometers of land. Minneapolis, London and Moscow were covered by more than a kilometer of ice. The oceans were a 100 meters lower. Nonetheless, people were making progress.<br>
Then, within less than 5000 years, the climate changed completely, nearly all the glaciers melted, the oceans rose, shorelines were inundated, rainfall patterns changed drastically, and average temperatures rose about 7 degrees C, and the extremes of temperatures changed even more. Nonetheless, people just kept making progress—extending their range to two more continents and eventually even landing on the moon. And this catastrophic climate change was only the latest in a whole series of hundreds of drastic changes that have bedeviled our species and our predecessor species for million of years; apparently without undue inconvenience for Hominids. <br>
Humans have the widest range of any species—from both poles to the Equator, from the sea (and even beneath) to all but the most extreme elevations. If our Pleistocene ancestors could handle multiple glaciations and de-glaciations without modern science, industrial technology, or even a college education; we should be able to handle a few blips on the weather radar.<br>
Our species has had so much experience handling drastic climate change, we should be pretty good at it by now. Listen to Mom and Dad Cro-Magnon discussing us: &quot;They're so nervous about everything--faint-hearted for people who've come so far. We couldn't afford to take our worries all that seriously. I wish they could be more sure-footed and unafraid. Lord knows they have nothing to fear compared to what we faced.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Climate change is a stick that greenies use to try to limmit our growth and an excuse that governents use to justify higher taxes. only 20 years ago the doom mongers were claiming that we were heading for an ice age.<br>
